## Notes on Method Choices

```{r inf2-notes, echo=FALSE, results='asis'}
cat(paste0(
  "- **Same test as the bubbles.** The p-values above come from `wilcox.test()` on log10 assay ",
  "values, TT vs TdaP, exactly as in `bubble_arm_effect()`. Only the effect *display* differs: the ",
  "bubbles show a bare difference of medians (no interval), whereas a forest plot needs one, so the ",
  "point/CI use the Hodges\u2013Lehmann shift and Wilcoxon `conf.int` \u2014 the estimator/interval that ",
  "belongs to this test. The raw `p` is identical to the bubble p.\n",
  "- **Orientation.** Everything is oriented **TdaP \u2212 TT** with **TT as the reference level**, so ",
  "the estimate is the effect of TdaP relative to TT (positive = higher with maternal TdaP), the ",
  "sign convention of Saso et al. 2026 Figure 2C/D. The `Direction` column reuses the bubble ",
  "labels (\u201cHigher TdaP\u201d / \u201cLower TdaP\u201d). Magnitudes and p-values are identical to the bubble ",
  "grid; only the displayed sign convention differs (the bubble reports median(TT) \u2212 median(TdaP)).\n",
  "- **Multiplicity.** Benjamini\u2013Hochberg is applied **within each assay class** (Whole = ",
  sum(inf2_stats$class == "Whole bacterium assays"), ", ADCD = ", sum(inf2_stats$class == "ADCD"),
  ", ADCP = ", sum(inf2_stats$class == "ADCP"), ", ADNP = ", sum(inf2_stats$class == "ADNP"),
  " tests), so each functional family is corrected on its own. To correct across the whole panel ",
  "instead, call `infmon2_arm_effect(..., by_class = FALSE)`; to change method, set `p_adjust_method`.\n",
  "- **Antigen coverage.** ADCP and ADNP have no FHA or FIM assays, so those cells are absent by design ",
  "(not missing data). ADCD spans all six antigens.\n",
  "- **Infant arms pooled.** This is the overall maternal effect at baseline. For an aP/wP-stratified ",
  "version, pass `infant_arm_sel = \"aP\"` / `\"wP\"` to `infmon2_arm_effect()`.\n"))
```
